as described below. You will need to do a bit of work from the command line. Julia takes some command line work. C++ probably does, I’ll be honest I have never installed it. If you flat-out do not want to do command line stuff, just go with MATLAB, but it makes me feel powerful to do command line stuff!","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"wB2YKfigB6"}],"key":"Y99l4IxUbK"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"MATLAB","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"qJyCfEN7lb"}],"identifier":"matlab","label":"MATLAB","html_id":"matlab","implicit":true,"key":"urESqiDRcj"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"MATLAB is the easiest to get going. As a CU student, you have free access if you create an account using your CU email address. Instructions are ","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"YmCpsYulqd"},{"type":"link","url":"https://oit.colorado.edu/software-hardware/software-catalog/matlab","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"ztGOJ6d4sM"}],"urlSource":"https://oit.colorado.edu/software-hardware/software-catalog/matlab","key":"Zt7EKiuyoa"},{"type":"text","value":" -- use the ones for students, under “How to get it”.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"dZ2gJx8e53"}],"key":"nVQUJ2EXrK"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once you have a MathWorks account and have it associated with the school’s license, you can choose to download a desktop version of MATLAB, or to access the cloud version of the software. (See the note below about toolboxes before installing!) Students in previous semesters have used both options, so you can decide what works best for you. However, if you use the online version, you must download the code and upload it to your GitHub repository. I like the immediate access of having MATLAB installed on my machine, and I think it runs a bit faster, but you can access your code from any computer if you are using the online version.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"b61vD891kC"}],"key":"e7NW0rEUgb"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The MathWorks site has many tutorials, maybe most notably the “MATLAB OnRamp”. ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"dLnpUg3W3V"},{"type":"link","url":"https://matlab.mathworks.com/","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can find it here","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"kkJpmztvUj"}],"urlSource":"https://matlab.mathworks.com/","key":"gxEH6RQywZ"},{"type":"text","value":"... it is an “Online Training”.","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"hlEj1bhf0N"}],"key":"meVwa8VhgO"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Toolboxes","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"hvPhupHLCB"}],"identifier":"toolboxes","label":"Toolboxes","html_id":"toolboxes","implicit":true,"key":"GJAruhW6xz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Basic MATLAB is going to be enough for the homework in this class, and you can always add toolboxes later. Some rec